    "summary": "After having worked in a interesting hospital environment at Radiology and Nuclear Medicine  with extra experience at Cath labs and  Operation Theater i moved to medical industry in 1989. \nI was responsible for selling and supporting equipment in MI (Molecular Imaging), X ray, CT  MR and medical films Already as of 1989 i was involved in first PACS and networked Workstations introductions, which was  my core business in Hermes Medical Solutions.\nIn Industry I was able to create and execute new business models for selling e.g. medical printers, Gamma Camera's and Pet/Ct systems. with success. \nMore recent in  \"Translate\"  a business venture within Philips Research, I was Sales and Marketing Manager.\nHere as a team we created a Medical Research Workstation for advanced image analysis in (pre) clinical US, PET, CT, SPECT and MRI that supported  Research in Radiology MI and the Radiotherapy environment.\n\nNext to selling direct I have been active and effective in supporting and setting up dealer business. \nI am a person who loves relationships and has matured them over the last 34 years in different companies.\nI love to work national and internationally and speak several European languages. \nNext to hat I do have a international network in Imaging and science.\n\nAs a team member i was initiating novel treatment technology for oncology treatment for which patent number pct/ib 2012/052063  was issued.\n\nI published a review article on SPECT reconstruction ( in Dutch), http://www.mtintegraal.nl/?p=80&editie=27&articleId=220",
